sprysound

Class PreloadedAudio

  • java.lang.Object
    • sprysound.Audio
      • sprysound.PreloadedAudio

  • public class PreloadedAudio
extends Audio
    Audio that loads it audio data completely into memory prior to being played. PreloadedAudio can be compared to StreamingAudio using the following attributes:

    • Functionality - Compared to StreamingAudio, PreloadedAudio offers extra functionality. Because PreloadedAudio loads all its audio data into memory, the duration of the audio can be determined (via the getLength method) and playback can occur at an arbitrary position (via the setPosition method).
    • Memory - Compared to PreloadedAudio, StreamingAudio uses less memory. PreloadedAudio requires memory equal to the size of its audio file, while StreamingAudio only needs enough memory for its read buffer.
    • Latency - PreloadedAudio will generally have less latency than StreamingAudio. PreloadedAudio has all of its audio data in memory and can therefore start playback immediately after a call to one of the play methods, while StreamingAudio will need to wait for its read buffer to be filled. In practice, any difference in latency is rarely noticeable.
    Author:
    Christian Holton
